═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
CRITICAL RULE — HOW TO FIND A SECTION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
A section starts with a heading line (often ALL CAPS, Title Case, or with emoji like 📝 💼 🔨).
The section content is the text that appears AFTER that heading, until the next heading.
NEVER return text that appears BEFORE the requested heading.
NEVER return the heading line itself — return ONLY the content under it.

